{"article_id":"bzd9NnIJTNxbiqWt","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Exactly six years after President Obama took office in the depths of the recession ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"the economy has finally improved enough","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"for the president","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"to brag about it Tuesday night in his annual State of the Union address .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Previewing his speech for audiences over the past two weeks ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Mr. Obama has recited the positive economic statistics so often","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"that he undoubtedly can do it in his sleep :","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"11 million private-sector jobs created over 58 straight months , the longest stretch of job growth in U.S. history .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Unemployment fell faster in 2014","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"than it had for 30 years ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"and now stands at 5.6 percent , the lowest jobless level since June 2008 .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"It ' s the kind of economic performance","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"that Mr. Obama has been promising since his first day in office on Jan. 20 , 2009 .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"But each year since then , a sluggish recovery had the president acknowledging","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"that there was \" more work to do . \"","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Now , from the resurgent auto industry","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"( a bailout","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"begun under President George W. Bush","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"and expanded by Mr. Obama )","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"to falling gas prices","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"( largely determined by global supply and demand ) ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Mr. Obama is taking full credit ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"after presiding over a weak economic recovery for nearly three-fourths of his presidency .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"\" There is good news","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"- the economy is finally coming back ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"and that ' s exactly what he ' s trumpeting , \"","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"said Charles Lipson , a professor of political science at the University of Chicago .","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"\" It ' s the one area","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"where he can claim plausibly bipartisan agreement ,","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"with both sides of the aisle clapping . \"","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"Troubling fiscal trends remain ,","depth":4},{"id":31,"text":"including a soaring national debt and stagnant wages .","depth":4},{"id":32,"text":"But senior administration officials say","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"Mr. Obama intends to use the improving economy as leverage","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"to call on Congress to approve a wide range of new federal programs","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"that would cost more than $ 230 billion , from universal government-paid tuition for community-college students to expanded tax breaks for the middle class .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"Obama ' s State of the Union guests include illegal immigrant , gun violence victim , Ebola doctor","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"To pay for those initiatives ,","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"the president wants to raise taxes on wealthier families by about $ 320 billion over 10 years ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"by raising the top rate on capital gains taxes to 28 percent","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"and eliminating a tax loophole for trust funds .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Mr. Obama also will propose charging a new fee on big banks .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"Congressional Republicans say","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"Mr. Obama ' s tax-hike plan is dead on arrival , a development","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"that will come as no surprise to the president and his advisers ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"who ' ve been watching the GOP reject tax increases for years .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"But analysts say","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Mr. Obama is setting the stage","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"to issue more executive actions over the next two years in areas","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"where Congress won ' t act ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"and also pounding on themes","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"he hopes","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"will put the GOP on the defensive","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"heading into the 2016 presidential election .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"\" It ' s not just about what gets passed this year ,","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"it ' s about who we elect in 2016 , \"","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"said Robert Lehrman , a professor of communications at American University","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"who was chief speechwriter for Vice President Al Gore .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"\" Obama may make a big pitch for free community-college tuition ,","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"and","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"even if it doesn ' t pass ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"he ' s thinking","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"Hillary","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"[ former Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton ]","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"can run against the Republicans on that .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"Even though they","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"[ White House officials ]","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"will say","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"they want to work in a bipartisan way ,","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"they know","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"the prospects are minimal . \"","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"With Republicans now in control of the Senate","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"and holding a larger majority in the House ,","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"some observers believe","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"it will free up Mr. Obama to confront the GOP more often .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"\" He ' s got nothing to lose , \"","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"said Richard Kelsey , assistant dean at the George Mason University law school .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"\" He doesn ' t have to pretend to cooperate with [ former Senate majority leader ] Harry Reid . \"","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"Since Democrats lost resoundingly in the midterm elections in November ,","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"Mr. Obama has been taking high-profile executive actions .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"He granted deportation amnesty in November to as many as five million illegal immigrants ,","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"and last month Mr. Obama announced","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"that he would normalize U.S. diplomatic relations with Cuba for the first time in more than 50 years .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"\" He ' s come out swinging , \"","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Mr. Kelsey said .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"\" The Republicans clobbered him ,","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"and the first thing","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"he did","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"was hand them a live hand grenade","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"[ deportation amnesty ]","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"with the pin pulled ,","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"and said ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"' What are you going to do about it ? '","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"And he found out","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"they weren ' t going to do anything about it ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"or they couldn ' t figure out what to do about it .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"He did a great job from a political standpoint .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"He turned around ,","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"took those election results","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"and stuffed them right back at the Republicans . \"","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Another reason","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"that Mr. Obama is likely to focus on the improving economy","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"is because his foreign policy is in trouble on several fronts .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"Denuclearization talks with Iran are making little progress ,","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"the threat of terrorist attacks","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"spawned in Syria and elsewhere","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"is multiplying ,","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"a trade deal with Pacific rim nations is still incomplete","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"and Russia is still agitating in Ukraine . \"","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"On Islamic terrorism , the utter failure of his policies in Syria , the total failure of the Russian re-set and greater danger there in the region , and what looks to be a very weak negotiating posture with Iran","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"that is already getting pushback from Congress ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"that he would like to keep the focus on his strong points and not his numerous weak points , \"","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"Mr. Lipson said .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"\" But with the events in Paris and in Brussels , he simply can ' t avoid talking about the larger problems . \"","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"The terrorist attacks two weeks ago in Paris and another plot","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"thwarted by authorities in Belgium","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"renewed concerns about the possibility of attacks in the U.S. ,","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"and raised criticism","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"that Mr. Obama and his advisers are deliberately downplaying the role of Islamist extremism in such violence .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"\" I would be shocked","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"if he uses the words ' Islamic terrorism , ' or ' jihadi ' in his speech , \"","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"Mr. Lipson said .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"\" He never speaks about that .","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"By failing to call this extremist Islamic-inspired violence","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"done in the name of Islam","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"for what it is ,","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"he simply can not think clearly about it .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"And I don ' t think","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"it ' s any of the president ' s business to act as theologians","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"and tell us what religions say .","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"It ' s not just that he ' s not an expert on it ,","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"it ' s that it ' s not the proper role of the president of the United States .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"We want him to be dealing with the policy problems","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"that are overwhelming him","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"and that the public is increasingly agitated about","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"and lacking in confidence","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"that he and his White House can cope with . \"","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"Immediately after his address , Mr. Obama will head out on the road","depth":6},{"id":142,"text":"to sell his proposals in familiar territory","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"- college campuses .","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"On Wednesday , the president will travel to Boise , Idaho ,","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"to speak to students at Boise State University .","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"On Thursday , he ' ll speak to students at the University of Kansas in Lawrence .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"By that time , Mr. Obama will probably be enjoying a slight \" bounce \" in the polls","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"that presidents usually experience after the State of the Union address .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"\" Every president gets a little uptick from the speech itself , \"","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"said Mr. Lehrman ,","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"who saw the challenge from the other side of the partisan divide","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"when he wrote the Democratic minority response to President George H.W . Bush ' s State of the Union address in 1989 .","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"the opposition party ' s speaker","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"- this year it will be freshman Republican Sen. Joni Earnst of Iowa -","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"is always at a disadvantage .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"\" It was a great lesson for me","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"- a nine-minute speech","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"with one person","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"sitting in the room , \"","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"Mr. Lehrman said .","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"\" I saw how ineffective it is .","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"How do you compete with the president ?","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"There ' s no way","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"you can . \"","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":331,"left":201,"right":330,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":195,"right":200,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":195,"left":188,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":169,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":0,"right":168,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":168,"left":1,"right":167,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":179,"right":186,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":179,"left":175,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":171,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":4,"right":170,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":170,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":7,"right":173,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":173,"left":172,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":176,"right":177,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearit